## Naming conventions

The generator applies a few consistent transforms over the Swift names. This is
the highest-value section of the guide — it's the one thing users can't get
from the native/third-party docs. Fill in the deltas that matter here:

| Swift | C# | Rule |
|---|---|---|
| `func load(...) async` | `LoadAsync(...)` | `async` methods gain an `Async` suffix and return `Task`/`Task<T>` |
| `obj.someValue` | `obj.SomeValue` | properties are PascalCase |
| `enum Foo { case bar(...) }` | `Foo` class with `.Tag` + `TryGetBar(out …)` | Swift enums-with-payload project to a class with a tag + `TryGet*` accessors |
