## Memory & threading

Generated types implement `ISwiftObject` / `IDisposable`. For short-lived
locals the finalizer cleans up, but `using var` is the recommended pattern for
deterministic cleanup — `Dispose` is safe on every generated type and
double-Dispose is a no-op.

```csharp
using var thing = new SomeType();
```

